title: HOUR 1- The Russell Westbrook Problem - Sep 07, 2020
itunes:title: HOUR 1- The Russell Westbrook Problem - Sep 07, 2020
description:
FOX Sports Radio hosts Jason Smith and Rob Parker are in for Dan and the Danettes, and the guys explain why the Houston Rockets have a Russell Westbrook problem that reared it's ugly head in Game 2 against the Los Angeles Lakers, and explain why we still don't really know which teams are actually good 40+ games through the MLB season. Plus, former NFL executive of the year Randy Mueller swings by to discuss why he thinks the Houston Texans overpaid for Deshaun Watson, what he's expecting from Cam Newton during his first season with the New England Patriots, and much more!
